cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY

The paper discusses an adaptation of Kohonen's Self Organizing Map (SOM) to (dis)similarity data, which is a common problem in data analysis. This makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to web log mining, which falls under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of (dis)similarity measures also suggests a possible fit with Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
